<topic id="undoing-and-redoing-user-actions">
  <title>The Undo/Redo Actions</title><prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>Text Editing Mode<indexterm>undo and redo</indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>The typical undo and redo actions are available in <ph keyref="product"/>:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><uicontrol>Undo</uicontrol> - menu <menucascade>
          <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Undo <shortcut>(Ctrl (Meta on Mac OS)+Z)</shortcut></uicontrol>
        </menucascade>
        <ph product="editor author developer">or the <uicontrol>
            <image href="../img/sa_undo_button.png"/> Undo </uicontrol> toolbar button</ph> -
        Reverses a maximum of 200 editing actions (configurable in the <xref
          href="preferences-editor.dita#preferences-editor" format="dita">Editor preferences
          page</xref>) to return to the preceding state.<note> Complex operations like
            <uicontrol>Replace All</uicontrol> or <uicontrol>Indent selection</uicontrol> count as a
          single undo event.</note></li>
      <li><uicontrol>Redo</uicontrol> - menu <menucascade>
          <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Redo <shortcut>(Ctrl+Y for Windows, Cmd+Shift+Z for Mac OSX and
              Linux)</shortcut></uicontrol>
        </menucascade>
        <ph product="editor author developer">or the <uicontrol>
            <image href="../img/sa_redo_button.png"/> Redo </uicontrol> toolbar button</ph> -
        Recreates a maximum of 100 editing actions that were undone by the
          <uicontrol>Undo</uicontrol> function.</li>
    </ul>
  </body>
</topic>